# GitHub Personal Access Token used at BUILD time to draw the per-repo
# "contributions per day" line graph on /github.
#
# The token is only needed for the named PUBLIC repo lines (any token works —
# classic or fine-grained — since it only reads public commit data).
#
# Private contributions do NOT come from the token (SAML SSO orgs like Sublime
# block token access anyway). They come from your PUBLIC profile contribution
# graph, which requires GitHub → Settings → Profile →
# "Include private contributions on my profile" to be ENABLED. They appear
# anonymized in the blue "Private / other" line.
#
# Local dev: copy this file to `.env` (already git-ignored) and fill it in.
# Cloudflare Pages: add GITHUB_TOKEN under Settings → Environment variables,
#   then trigger a new build. Without it, the page falls back to the heatmap.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Substack publication used to pull inline blog posts (the /blog reader pages).
# Optional — defaults to https://lukemadethat.substack.com in src/lib/substack.ts.
# Set this only if you rename the publication or move to a custom domain.
SUBSTACK_URL=

